  "llm_summary": "Flat A in Toa Payoh offers the most mature amenity profile of the three, with a hawker centre just 150m away and Toa Payoh MRT within a 4-minute walk, providing excellent connectivity via the North-South Line. Flat B in Ang Mo Kio has the advantage of a lower-distance hawker centre at 210m and is located close to AMK Hub for retail needs, though its MRT access at 640m is the furthest of the three. Flat C in Punggol is situated in a newer estate and has the highest concentration of primary schools within 1km — four in total, including Mee Toh and Punggol Green Primary — making it particularly well-positioned for families with school-going children, though its distance to the MRT station and shopping mall is the greatest among the three."
